com.thomsonreuters.ema.access

Interface FieldEntry


  • public interface FieldEntry
    FieldEntry represents an entry of FieldList.

    FieldEntry associates entry's field id, name, data and its data type.

    See Also:
    Data, ComplexType, ReqMsg, RefreshMsg, UpdateMsg, StatusMsg, GenericMsg, PostMsg, AckMsg, FieldList, ElementList, Map, Vector, Series, FilterList, OmmOpaque, OmmXml, OmmAnsiPage, OmmError

    • Method Detail

      • loadType

        int loadType()
        Returns the DataType of the entry's load. Return of DataType.DataTypes.NO_DATA signifies no data present in load. Return of DataType.DataTypes.ERROR signifies error while extracting content of load.
        Returns:
        data type of the contained object

      • code

        int code()
        Returns the Code of the entry's load. The code indicates a special state of a Data. Attempts to extract data will cause OmmInvalidUsageException if Data.DataCode.BLANK is returned.
        Returns:
        data code of the contained object

        Returns:

        int fieldId()
        Returns FieldId.
        Returns:
        field id

      • name

        java.lang.String name()
        Returns acronym field name associated to the FieldId from the field dictionary. Returns empty string if FieldId is not found in field dictionary.
        Returns:
        String containing name of the entry

      • rippleTo

        int rippleTo(int fieldId)
        Returns a ripple FieldId if the current entry has a ripple field. A subsequent call using the former non-zero return value as a formal parameter, returns the next ripple field in a ripple sequence. Returns zero if no ripple field or the final ripple field of a ripple sequence.
        Parameters:
        fieldId - field id value
        Returns:
        field id
